snippet.textDisplay: I've went from black to blonde in 24 hours. 30 volume and 2 oz white no blue/filler bleach. That process 4 times 40 mins each with a wash and oil in between air-dry each time. Then one more time with that process for 25 minutes,  toner and then always have a natural oil like grapeseed oil and a thickener oil like smooth'nshine for UV protection for the raw oil I put on my hair first. My normal hair is wavy, thick, and medium coarse.
snippet.textOriginal: I've went from black to blonde in 24 hours. 30 volume and 2 oz white no blue/filler bleach. That process 4 times 40 mins each with a wash and oil in between air-dry each time. Then one more time with that process for 25 minutes,  toner and then always have a natural oil like grapeseed oil and a thickener oil like smooth'nshine for UV protection for the raw oil I put on my hair first. My normal hair is wavy, thick, and medium coarse.

snippet.textDisplay:
Edit: forgot to say. Every Hair stylist has ALWAYS started at my roots too. I wouldn’t know that’s wasn’t ok until Brad told me.

What do I have to do to get a “real” hair color professional like Brad to do my hair?? I’m a natural blonde that gets blonde highlights. Just so I have dimension. And it’s never good!! I’ve tried so many salons, so many stylists. When brad said “do you think we go into the back and mix box dye”. That’s exactly what I think some of these “professionals” do. I just paid $160 a few days ago and she didn’t even tone my hair after. Just rinsed and blowed dried. I did learn a few years ago to specifically ask for a color specialist. Nope, doesn’t matter where I live. how do they mess up blonde highlights on a blonde 😭 😭
